18
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:50,429
Haifeng Radio International FM99.7 is about to broadcast the host Qian Kaiyi…

19
00:01:50,429 --> 00:01:51,880
Countdown to show recording.

20
00:01:51,880 --> 00:01:55,350
Four. Three. Two. One.

21
00:01:55,350 --> 00:01:56,710
[ON AIR]

22
00:01:59,620 --> 00:02:01,410
Today is Valentine's Day.

23
00:02:01,410 --> 00:02:05,609
Many friends from the audience have sent messages of love stories with their boyfriends.

24
00:02:05,609 --> 00:02:11,880
So on this special festive occasion, I also have some good news to tell you.

25
00:02:11,880 --> 00:02:14,390
What good news are you going to share?

26
00:02:14,390 --> 00:02:16,600
A'Yi has confessed his love to me.

27
00:02:18,620 --> 00:02:20,110
Stop recording for now.

28
00:02:20,110 --> 00:02:21,710
What nonsense are you talking about, Fang Yuxuan?

29
00:02:21,710 --> 00:02:24,829
How can you make a joke like this? Do you have any sense of propriety?

30
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,630
Sorry.

31
00:02:27,630 --> 00:02:30,000
Explain to the radio station after a while.

32
00:02:32,190 --> 00:02:34,360
Qian Kaiyi,

33
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:38,539
is it you really don't fall for me or you dare not admit you do?

34
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:43,360
Fang Yuxuan, I really don't fall for you.

35
00:02:43,360 --> 00:02:46,960
But affections can be developed.

36
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:50,499
After being together for a long time, affections will grow. You can give it a try.

37
00:02:50,499 --> 00:02:53,090
Are you going explain to the radio station or not?

38
00:02:53,090 --> 00:02:56,429
Given my relationship with you as a colleague, I show you respect again and again.

39
00:02:56,429 --> 00:02:59,099
But I tell you what, Fang Yuxuan, this will be the last time.

40
00:02:59,099 --> 00:03:02,989
If you mess things up again, either you go or I go.

41
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:05,820
Well…

42
00:03:05,820 --> 00:03:08,230
He Dun, I'm really not related to her in any way.

43
00:03:08,230 --> 00:03:10,710
She came to the wedding reception that day just to get back at me.

44
00:03:10,710 --> 00:03:14,679
Do you know what your only solution to this matter is?

45
00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:18,910
I shouldn't have gone to the wedding reception that day in the first place.

46
00:03:18,910 --> 00:03:21,969
- No, don't. Didn't you—
- Don't follow me.

47
00:03:21,969 --> 00:03:24,540
Didn't you save Shasha and Xiao Yuan that day?

48
00:03:24,540 --> 00:03:27,340
What's more, it was such a wonderful thing.

49
00:03:27,340 --> 00:03:30,520
He Dun, what are you exactly angry about?

50
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:33,720
About me or Fang Yuxuan?

51
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:36,099
I'm angry about me, me. I'm angry about myself, all right?

52
00:03:36,099 --> 00:03:39,600
Well, you…you…don't…

53
00:04:03,740 --> 00:04:07,460
[Personality Psychology]

54
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:12,529
[Transference and Counter-transference]
Let's first talk about what counter-transference is.

55
00:04:12,529 --> 00:04:16,530
In a broad sense, counter-transference encompasses the emotional responses

56
00:04:16,530 --> 00:04:19,000
of all counselors to their visitors.

57
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:20,539
Any conflict related to their family experiences,

58
00:04:20,539 --> 00:04:24,230
gender roles, parenting roles and unmet needs

59
00:04:24,230 --> 00:04:27,600
is likely to lead to counter-transference.

60
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:31,449
A visitor wants the counselor to give him

61
00:04:31,449 --> 00:04:34,909
the attention and affirmation that he didn't get from his father.

62
00:04:34,909 --> 00:04:38,439
And the counselor also wants to show his importance

63
00:04:38,439 --> 00:04:40,479
through a dependent relationship.

64
00:04:40,479 --> 00:04:45,209
So the counselor is highly likely to accept the visitor's dependence unconsciously.

65
00:04:46,230 --> 00:04:50,309
Lili, we've lost internet connection again. When are you going to get it fixed?

66
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:53,400
Jiahui?

67
00:04:56,720 --> 00:05:00,019
I've called Mr. Ye to come over. Didn't he come just in time?

68
00:05:00,019 --> 00:05:03,929
He just came back from my house. Now you are putting him out again.

69
00:05:04,570 --> 00:05:06,780
Jiahui, I'm sorry. I've put you out again.

70
00:05:06,780 --> 00:05:09,419
It's All right. I've fixed it.

71
00:05:09,419 --> 00:05:13,200
Anything you ask for, I'll certainly come as soon as I can. See if you can get connected now.

72
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:14,220
All right.

73
00:05:14,220 --> 00:05:18,600
The two of us worked on it for quite a few days and didn't fix it. You got it done in a heartbeat.

74
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:19,760
It's good now, connected.

75
00:05:19,760 --> 00:05:21,550
Would you like me to add an app for you?

76
00:05:21,550 --> 00:05:24,570
So that you can monitor everything going on at home anytime when you are outside.

77
00:05:24,570 --> 00:05:27,650
If it's convenient for you, then… please.

78
00:05:29,570 --> 00:05:34,209
Mr. Ye is such a professional. Shouldn't you thank him kindly?

79
00:05:34,209 --> 00:05:37,179
Let me make you a cup of coffee. Just a moment.

80
00:05:38,270 --> 00:05:40,650
I'll go and slice some fruit for you.

81
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:52,030
This is your opportunity...

82
00:05:58,450 --> 00:06:00,650
He's so good.

83
00:06:01,610 --> 00:06:04,519
Both presentable and professional. An added bonus.

84
00:06:06,790 --> 00:06:08,550
He's my neighbor.

85
00:06:08,550 --> 00:06:12,160
I've put him out the whole day. I can't pay back his favor.

86
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:14,890
I'd say he's only too keen to come to our house every day.

87
00:06:14,890 --> 00:06:17,840
He should thank me for asking him over.

88
00:06:22,940 --> 00:06:24,580
[Qian Kaiyi]

89
00:06:25,930 --> 00:06:27,770
Why are you nervous?

90
00:06:41,850 --> 00:06:43,500
Jiahui.

91
00:06:45,340 --> 00:06:47,010
Thank you.

92
00:06:50,270 --> 00:06:52,430
I'll let you guys talk first. I'm going upstairs first. I've got things to do.

93
00:06:52,430 --> 00:06:54,450
Take your time.

94
00:07:01,160 --> 00:07:02,630
Take a seat.

95
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:07,880
I've downloaded your app for you.

96
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:09,400
Thanks.

97
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:14,350
You've helped me so much, I don't even know how to repay your kindness.

98
00:07:14,350 --> 00:07:15,830
Can I make a request?

99
00:07:15,830 --> 00:07:16,880
Sure, you can.

100
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:19,120
How about going on a date with me?

101
00:07:20,580 --> 00:07:22,830
You are such a smart cookie.

102
00:07:22,830 --> 00:07:26,510
My billing rate is expensive. I usually charge by the hour, all right?

103
00:07:26,510 --> 00:07:29,939
No problem. As long as you make out an invoice to me.

104
00:07:29,939 --> 00:07:31,720
You are humorous.

105
00:07:36,540 --> 00:07:38,100
He Dun,

106
00:07:38,950 --> 00:07:41,060
I know you are reluctant at heart.

107
00:07:41,880 --> 00:07:45,469
It's all right. I won't force your hand.

108
00:07:46,380 --> 00:07:49,339
I'm going for now. Call me again if you need my help for anything.

109
00:07:51,830 --> 00:07:53,480
Jiahui.

110
00:07:57,720 --> 00:07:59,980
I accept your invitation.

111
00:08:07,230 --> 00:08:08,670
Rest easy.

112
00:08:08,670 --> 00:08:12,920
A date with me is certainly better than the one with those short-tempered people.

113
00:08:25,750 --> 00:08:27,100
[Qian Kaiyi]

114
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:45,530
[Qian Kaiyi]

115
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:53,110
He Dun, you've finally answered my call.

116
00:08:53,110 --> 00:08:55,879
I was busy just now. I didn't look at my cellphone. What's the matter?

117
00:08:55,879 --> 00:08:59,359
You left in a hurry. I forgot to ask you about something.

118
00:08:59,359 --> 00:09:01,330
How's our mother doing?

119
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:04,880
I'm going to hang up if you have nothing else to say.

120
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:06,369
I'll cut a long story short.

121
00:09:06,369 --> 00:09:09,009
It's the same thing I told you about in the WeChat group this afternoon.

122
00:09:09,009 --> 00:09:13,199
Since our show is a smash hit, the radio station allocated a sizable sum of money for our publicity.

123
00:09:13,199 --> 00:09:16,349
Come to the radio station tomorrow afternoon for a poster shooting.

124
00:09:16,349 --> 00:09:19,259
What poster? Me and you in a poster?

125
00:09:19,259 --> 00:09:21,710
Well, this is the radio station's routine publicity model.

126
00:09:21,710 --> 00:09:23,550
I've done it before.

127
00:09:23,550 --> 00:09:25,720
It's done mainly to give the audience a visual impression.

128
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:29,539
So when they are listening to our show, there will be a 3D stereoscopic effect that can bring us closer

129
00:09:29,539 --> 00:09:33,760
[Time Interview]
to the audience and to each other.

130
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:35,300
A versatilely matched duo.

131
00:09:35,300 --> 00:09:37,750
It'll be done with just a few clicks of the shutter.

132
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:44,470
He Dun. Are you hearing me?

133
00:09:44,470 --> 00:09:45,950
[Qian Kaiyi]

134
00:10:00,660 --> 00:10:03,250
What's wrong with her again?

135
00:10:03,250 --> 00:10:05,419
He Dun, are you being jealous?

136
00:10:05,419 --> 00:10:06,859
What can I be jealous of?

137
00:10:06,859 --> 00:10:10,039
It's such an important thing. Shouldn't he tell me about it beforehand?

138
00:10:10,039 --> 00:10:12,590
But he didn't tell me until now. Isn't that a disrespect to me?

139
00:10:12,590 --> 00:10:14,810
If it were you, would you not be angry?

140
00:10:14,810 --> 00:10:18,710
Yes.

141
00:10:18,710 --> 00:10:21,180
But there are exceptions.

142
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:25,280
Like Mr. Ye next door.

143
00:10:25,280 --> 00:10:27,030
He's meticulous and gentlemanly.

144
00:10:27,030 --> 00:10:30,239
He gives acupuncture therapy to your mother and fixes our internet.

145
00:10:30,239 --> 00:10:32,880
The thing is, he's never asked for anything.

146
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:35,449
If you guys are together later on,

147
00:10:35,449 --> 00:10:38,529
won't you be able to save the money for your mother's physiotherapy?

148
00:10:38,529 --> 00:10:42,269
Are you looking for a boyfriend or a physiotherapist for me?

149
00:10:42,269 --> 00:10:45,780
Well, it's good to have the best of both worlds.

150
00:10:45,780 --> 00:10:48,000
Isn't it?

151
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:53,199
But I kept worrying all the time if he'd take things too hard.

152
00:10:53,199 --> 00:10:56,359
He's quite a nice guy indeed. He has a sense of propriety.

153
00:10:56,359 --> 00:10:59,019
He's quite sensible and good at taking care of people.

154
00:10:59,019 --> 00:11:01,829
But it's not that he asks for nothing at all.

155
00:11:01,829 --> 00:11:06,229
Something is going on, He Dun. Is it like what I thought?

156
00:11:06,229 --> 00:11:09,399
He… He asked me to go on a date with him just now.

157
00:11:09,399 --> 00:11:13,499
It's you to blame. You always put him out for no good reason.

158
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:24,439
He Dun, you've always been a person with professional ethics in my eyes.

159
00:11:25,090 --> 00:11:26,140
[Incoming Messages: Qian Kaiyi]

160
00:11:26,140 --> 00:11:28,300
He Dun, shall we play Rock-Paper-Scissors?

161
00:11:28,300 --> 00:11:31,329
One round will do, come to have your photo taken if you lose.

162
00:11:31,329 --> 00:11:35,310
If you don't reply, don't blame me for calling the shots for you.

163
00:11:40,030 --> 00:11:43,390
Stop sending me messages. Do whatever you like.

164
00:11:46,230 --> 00:11:49,690
Brother Kaiyi, you see, it's such a late hour

165
00:11:49,690 --> 00:11:52,060
and you still don't let me off work.

166
00:11:53,110 --> 00:11:54,340
All right. Go home first.

167
00:11:54,340 --> 00:11:56,820
- Leave the laptop with me.
- All right.

168
00:12:03,250 --> 00:12:06,770
Long-haired beauty.

169
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:28,550
[Qian Kaiyi: Want to go see a movie? I'm sure you'll like it. Want to go?]

170
00:14:12,540 --> 00:14:15,440
Instead of sleeping in the middle of the night, what are you coming to my place for?

171
00:14:15,440 --> 00:14:18,029
Lili, He Dun's been giving me the cold shoulder for two days.

172
00:14:18,029 --> 00:14:20,230
Did I do anything wrong to cause misunderstanding on her part?

173
00:14:20,230 --> 00:14:21,840
There's something off about you lately.

174
00:14:21,840 --> 00:14:22,909
In what way?

175
00:14:22,909 --> 00:14:24,540
Are you not sleeping in the middle of the night and coming to my place

176
00:14:24,540 --> 00:14:26,640
just because she's giving you the cold shoulder?

177
00:14:26,640 --> 00:14:31,110
No, I'm worrying if I've done anything wrong to make her unhappy.

178
00:14:31,110 --> 00:14:33,040
Well…

179
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:34,150
No problem.

180
00:14:34,150 --> 00:14:35,550
You are not sleeping and coming to my place instead.

181
00:14:35,550 --> 00:14:37,940
This is not like what an ordinary colleague would do.

182
00:14:37,940 --> 00:14:41,299
Whether as her friend or colleague or in whatever capacity,

183
00:14:41,299 --> 00:14:43,770
I just don't want her to be unhappy.

184
00:14:44,840 --> 00:14:47,110
All right, I'll help you once more.

185
00:14:47,110 --> 00:14:50,819
- Thanks.
- A treat of Michelin dinner.

186
00:14:56,470 --> 00:14:58,080
He Dun!

187
00:15:00,670 --> 00:15:02,500
What's up with you?

188
00:15:02,500 --> 00:15:04,320
He Dun.

189
00:15:05,250 --> 00:15:07,250
Why are you crying?

190
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:11,000
Tell me. What happened?

191
00:15:11,860 --> 00:15:13,900
What happened?

192
00:15:22,910 --> 00:15:25,790
- He Dun…
- He Dun.

193
00:15:29,280 --> 00:15:30,770
He Dun!

194
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:39,590
He Dun!

195
00:15:41,810 --> 00:15:43,750
What's up with you?

196
00:15:45,710 --> 00:15:49,289
- Can I have a word with you?
- I don't want to talk now.

197
00:15:49,289 --> 00:15:51,660
- Are you feeling unwell?
- No.

198
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:54,420
I only have a few words to say.

199
00:15:54,420 --> 00:15:56,400
I don't want to listen.

200
00:15:56,400 --> 00:15:58,809
If I make you unhappy, you can hit me or curse me.

201
00:15:58,809 --> 00:16:02,439
You can do whatever you like to me. But don't be unhappy, all right?

202
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:06,599
It has nothing to do with you. It's already in the past, all right?

203
00:16:06,599 --> 00:16:08,109
Let's not bring it up again.

204
00:16:08,109 --> 00:16:10,870
If it has nothing to do with me, then to whom?

205
00:16:11,810 --> 00:16:14,200
He Dun… Jun Jun!

206
00:16:14,969 --> 00:16:17,790
Can you stop calling me Jun Jun?

207
00:16:18,810 --> 00:16:20,690
What's wrong?

208
00:16:22,470 --> 00:16:25,060
Jun Jun is not my pet name at all.

209
00:16:26,150 --> 00:16:28,770
Why does auntie also call you Jun Jun?

210
00:16:32,010 --> 00:16:34,670
Jun Jun used to be my younger brother's name.

211
00:16:36,440 --> 00:16:39,650
My younger brother died when he was eight.

212
00:16:40,670 --> 00:16:42,550
Jun Jun!

213
00:17:06,230 --> 00:17:08,050
I'm sorry.

214
00:17:08,050 --> 00:17:10,660
I just got to know you had a younger brother.

215
00:17:13,300 --> 00:17:15,330
I didn't mean to.

216
00:17:18,230 --> 00:17:20,730
I know you didn't.

217
00:17:20,730 --> 00:17:24,419
Otherwise I wouldn't be here to explain so much to you.

218
00:17:24,419 --> 00:17:26,290
I would have left long ago.

219
00:17:27,590 --> 00:17:30,870
I just hope after telling you so much,

220
00:17:30,870 --> 00:17:34,179
you'll stop doing things that bug me.

221
00:17:38,070 --> 00:17:41,289
Do you know what is the most common thing in this city?

222
00:17:46,880 --> 00:17:49,190
It's sand.

223
00:17:49,190 --> 00:17:53,100
There used to be a time when I especially enjoyed seeing the sea.

224
00:17:53,100 --> 00:17:55,159
Actually, I was not seeing the sea.

225
00:17:55,159 --> 00:17:58,920
I just liked poking a few holes on the beach,

226
00:17:59,800 --> 00:18:01,710
because it wouldn't be long

227
00:18:01,710 --> 00:18:04,960
before the waves smoothed out the holes.

228
00:18:04,960 --> 00:18:08,159
Then I would guess how many waves it took

229
00:18:08,159 --> 00:18:11,130
to smooth out the holes completely.

230
00:18:11,130 --> 00:18:15,329
If I guess right, I'd treat myself to a big meal.

231
00:18:19,500 --> 00:18:21,310
Thank you for your comfort.

232
00:18:21,310 --> 00:18:26,219
But I don't think there is such a word as empathy in this world.

233
00:18:26,219 --> 00:18:29,519
Maybe not being able to empathize is a kind of luck instead.

234
00:18:37,160 --> 00:18:38,590
He Dun,

235
00:18:39,360 --> 00:18:44,259
if you need a special listener one day, just turn around.

236
00:18:44,259 --> 00:18:46,040
I'm sure I'll be there.

237
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:12,110
Jun Jun should be your pet name.

238
00:19:12,110 --> 00:19:14,560
I'll call you by that name from now on.

239
00:19:14,560 --> 00:19:17,960
- Jun Jun—
- Can you stay away from me? Please.

240
00:19:18,929 --> 00:19:20,680
Sorry, He Dun.

241
00:19:22,280 --> 00:19:24,459
Did I do anything wrong?

242
00:19:24,459 --> 00:19:26,360
- If it's because—
- The safety distance between people is 1.2 meters.

243
00:19:26,360 --> 00:19:29,030
Once you pass beyond it, I'd think you are threatening me.

244
00:19:29,030 --> 00:19:32,069
Let me know if I've done anything wrong, I'll apologize to you.

245
00:19:32,069 --> 00:19:33,950
The problem lies with me.

246
00:19:42,950 --> 00:19:45,399
If I make you unhappy, you can hit me or curse me.

247
00:19:45,399 --> 00:19:47,829
You can do whatever you like to me, But don't be unhappy, all right?

248
00:19:47,829 --> 00:19:50,459
